    "Commentary Vol. 139": "And the priest shall burn it upon the altar, etc.] The fat of the\ntail, of the inwards, the two kidneys, and the caul of the liver:\n[it is] the food of the offering made by fire unto the Lord; or \u201cbread\u201d; this\npart of the offering that was burnt belonged to the Lord; it was his food,\nand what was accepted of by him, and therefore is elsewhere called the\n[v_Lev_21_8] bread of God, (<032108>Leviticus 21:8,22 <042802>Numbers 28:2).\nVer.",
